In [16]:
def k_distances(x, k):#k
    
    dim0 = x.shape[0]
    
    #x.dot(x.T)=dim0dim0
    #np.sum(x**2, axis=1).T = dim011
    #np.repeat(np.sum(x**2, axis=1),dim0,axis=0)reshape(dim0,dim0) = dim0dim0dim0
    p=-2*x.dot(x.T)+np.sum(x**2, axis=1).T+ np.repeat(np.sum(x**2, axis=1),dim0,axis=0).reshape(dim0,dim0)
    
    p = np.sqrt(p) #ijxixjdim0dim0
    p.sort(axis=1) #
    p=p[:,k] #k
    p.sort() #
    return p

m= k_distances(X, 4) #k=minpts=4
plt.plot(m)
plt.ylabel("k-distances")
plt.grid(True)
plt.show()
